{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida7e35482-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"583"},"text":"§ 583.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this chapter:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida7e35483-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “promotion zone” means a promotion eligibility category consisting of officers on a warrant officer active-duty list in the same grade (or the same grade and competitive category) who—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida7e35484-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of grades below chief warrant officer, W–5, have neither (i) failed of selection for promotion to the next higher grade, nor (ii) been removed from a list of warrant officers recommended for promotion to that grade (other than after having been placed on that list after a selection from below the promotion zone); and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida7e35485-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" are senior to the warrant officer designated by the Secretary concerned to be the junior warrant officer in the promotion zone eligible for promotion to the next higher grade.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida7e35486-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “warrant officers above the promotion zone” means a group of officers on a warrant officer active-duty list in the same grade (or the same grade and competitive category) who—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida7e35487-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" are eligible for consideration for promotion to the next higher grade;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida7e35488-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" are in the same grade as warrant officers in the promotion zone; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida7e35489-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" are senior to the senior warrant officer in the promotion zone.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida7e3548a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “warrant officers below the promotion zone” means a group of officers on a warrant officer active-duty list in the same grade (or the same grade and competitive category) who—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida7e3548b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" are eligible for consideration for promotion to the next higher grade;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida7e3548c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" are in the same grade as warrant officers in the promotion zone; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida7e3548d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583/3/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" are junior to the junior warrant officer in the promotion zone.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida7e3548e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s583/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The active-duty list referred to in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s573/b"},"text":"section 573(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":" includes the active-duty promotion list established by section 41a "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002037"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002037"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of title 14."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida7e3548f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attr